result.title: The Shawshank Redemption
result.overview: Red (Morgan Freeman) and Andy (Tim Robbins), both incarcerated at Shawshank prison, forge an unlikely bond that will span more than twenty years. Together they discover hope as the ultimate means of survival, in a poignant tale of the human spirit.

result.title: Toy Story
result.overview: Welcome to an astonishing world where toys play while their owners are away. Meet Woody, Buzz and all their friends in an adventure filled with humor, heart and friendship.

result.title: Bloodline
result.overview: Tells the suspenseful story of an attractive and privileged woman who inherits the controlling interest of the family-owned pharmaceutical empire, following the mysterious death of her father and, almost immediately, finds her own life in jeopardy.

result.title: Good Will Hunting
result.overview: Will Hunting is the most brilliant mind at MIT and a headstrong, working-class genius who‚Äôs failing the lessons of life. After too many run-ins with the law, Will‚Äôs last chance is a psychology professor who might be the only man who can reach him!

result.title: The Last Temptation of Christ
result.overview: Director Martin Scorsese's stellar film adaptation of the controversial novel: Jesus questions the nature of his higher calling while imagining his life as an ordinary man.

result.title: My Own Private Idaho
result.overview: Two best friends living on the streets of Portland as hustlers embark on a journey of self discovery and find their relationship stumbling along the way.

result.title: Take Shelter
result.overview: Plagued by a series of apocalyptic visions, Curtis LaForche, a young husband and father, questions whether to shelter his family from a coming storm, or from himself. As he tries desperately to stay sane, his obsessive actions become ever more erratic, placing his livelihood, his marriage and eventually his health in jeopardy.

result.title: Dallas Buyers Club
result.overview: Based on the true story of Ron Woodroof (Matthew McConaughey), whose life was overturned when he was diagnosed with HIV and given thirty days to live. Bereft of government-approved effective medicines, Woodroof decides to take matters into his own hands.

result.title: Pan's Labyrinth
result.overview: A faun charges a girl with three dangerous tasks, which she must complete to achieve immortality.

result.title: Ghost in the Shell
result.overview: In the near future, Major Mira Killian is the first of her kind: a human saved from a terrible crash, who is cyber-enhanced to be a perfect soldier devoted to stopping the world's most dangerous criminals.

result.title: Ghost in the Shell
result.overview: Influencing filmmakers from the Wachowskis to James Cameron, Mamoru Oshii‚Äôs cyberpunk classic is one of the defining anime of its generation. A dystopian vision jeweled with glass-walled skyscrapers and automatons, whose hypnotic beauty begs the fundamental question of what it means to be human.

result.title: Ender's Game
result.overview: As fears of an alien invasion grow, Earth's International Fleet recruits an unlikely leader - a young and brilliant boy - to command its forces and fight for the future of the human race. Based on the worldwide best-selling/award winning novel.

result.title: Fifty Shades Darker
result.overview: When Christian tries to entice Ana back into his life, she demands a new arrangement before giving him another chance. As they rebuild trust, shadowy figures from Christian‚Äôs past reappear, determined to destroy their hopes for a future together.

result.title: The Hobbit: The Desolation of Smaug
result.overview: Based on the book by J.R.R. Tolkien.

result.title: Mary Shelley's Frankenstein
result.overview: Dr. Victor Frankenstein (Kenneth Branagh) obsessively experiments with the possibilities of man-made creation. After finally bringing a creature (Robert DeNiro) to life, however, he realizes too late the full horror of what he has done.

result.title: Shell
result.overview: Shell is a 17-year-old woman, who lives and works at a petrol station in the Scottish Highlands. Apart from the customers who call by for fuel, and a few regulars who acknowledge and catch up with her, Shell's only company is her reserved and softly spoken father, to whom she is devoted. Beautifully photographed, Shell is a deeply affecting story with quiet, emotionally charged performances.

result.title: 6 Souls
result.overview: A forensic psychiatrist must race against time to unravel a baffling case of multiple personalities.

result.title: Run Hide Fight
result.overview: 17-year-old Zoe Hull uses her wits, survival skills, and compassion to fight for her life, and those of her fellow classmates, against a group of live-streaming shooters.

result.title: Shelter
result.overview: Zach put aside aspirations for art school to help out his family, but a summer romance with his friend's brother forces him to make important decisions about his life.

result.title: Shelter
result.overview: A homeless immigrant (Anthony Mackie) and heroin addict (Jennifer Connelly) form an unlikely relationship that will change their lives forever.

result.title: We Need to Do Something
result.overview: Tensions simmer and nerves begin to fray as a family realize that untold evil is lurking beyond their walls, in this dread-inducing thrill ride from the executive producer of the Saw franchise. After Melissa and her family seek shelter from a storm, they become trapped. With no sign of rescue, hours turn to days and Melissa comes to realize that she and her girlfriend Amy might have something to do with the horrors that threaten to tear her family - and the entire world ‚Äì apart.

result.title: Harlan Coben's Shelter
result.overview: Based on the bestselling series by Harlan Coben, Shelter follows the story of Mickey Bolitar after the death of his father leads him to start a new life in suburban New Jersey. When another new student disappears, Mickey finds himself tangled in a web of secrets. With the help of two new friends, Spoon and Ema, they reveal a dark underground that may hold the answers to decades of disappearances.
